ZCZC GE04
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 172300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE CENTRES ARE EXP TO LIE OVER ICELAND AND
WALES. OVERNIGHT AND THROUGH SUNDAY THE LOW ACROSS ICELAND WILL MOV SLWY
E INTO THE N OF CULLERCOATS WHILST THE LOW OVER WALES WILL MOV SLWY SEWARDS
INTO FRANCE AND FILL. PRESSURE WILL THEN BUILD FM THE SW AND BY MIDDAY ON
MONDAY A TRANSIENT RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP ACROSS THE UK. THIS RIDGE
WILL THEN COLLAPSES SEWARDS AS A LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM SPREADS IN FM THE NW.
BY MIDDAY TUESDAY THERE IS SOME SIG UNCERTAINTY HOWEVER THIS LOW IS CURRENTLY
SIGNALLED TO LIE ACROSS NERN IRELAND MOV E. ON SUNDAY STRG WINDS MAY TEMPO
DEVELOP ACROSS THE NW OF CULLERCOATS BEFORE EASING OVERNIGHT. ON MONDAY
EVENING AND OVERNIGHT NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP TO SPREAD E ACROSS CULLERCOATS.
WINDS ARE THEN LIKELY TO EASE TO STRG TUESDAY
